= Introduction to Linear Algebra

#lettrine[
  Linear Algebra is one of the most fundamental branches of mathematics. Do not be fooled by its simplicity, though: it gets difficult as soon as you lose track of what the objects actually represent. This short guide will always start from a geometric, visual intuition before explaining the numerical algorithms.
  Whenever you learn a new topic in Linear Algebra, ask yourself: *what does this represent in space?* I promise it makes hard problems far easier to solve. This is because you'll find it way easier to understand the problem at a deeper level by visualizing them.
]

\
If you find yourself in need of an actual definition for what Linear Algebra _is_:

#definition(title: "Linear Algebra")[
  Linear Algebra is the study of *linear maps* on finite-dimensional *vector spaces*.
]

So to understand Linear Algebra at the most basic level, you need:

1. vector spaces
2. linear maps
